{"lemma":"هِيت","slug":"هِيت","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"هِيت","root":"هيت","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n41473","n41475"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%87%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AA"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n41473","headword_ar":"هَيْتَ","root":"hyt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an exclamation denoting wonder: the Arabs say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayota liloHilomi","text_ar":"هَيْتَ لِلْحِلْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What forbearing mildness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clemency!"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayota laka","text_ar":"هَيْتَ لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Akh, S, K, &c.,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayoti lk","text_ar":"هَيْتِ لك"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Akh, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayota lk","text_ar":"هَيْتَ لك"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Akh, IB, K,) and the first letter is sometimes with kesreh; (K;) as is related on the authority of 'Alee, (TA,) [so that you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiyta","text_ar":"هِيتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiyti","text_ar":"هِيتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiytu","text_ar":"هِيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the first of which three forms is mentioned by Fr, Akh, IB, and the third by Fr, IB; but for the second I find no other authority than that implied above;] of all which, the most common is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayota lk","text_ar":"هَيْتَ لك"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-hah to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Zj:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayota","text_ar":"هَيْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the dial. of Howrán, whence it became introduced into Mekkeh; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiyta","text_ar":"هِيتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of the dial. of El-Medeeneh: (Fr:) [imper. verbal ns.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halum~a","text_ar":"هَلُمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Come!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Akh, S, L, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEaAla","text_ar":"تَعَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"the same, (Fr, Ks,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqobilo","text_ar":"اَقْبِلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the same, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Come forward!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) It occurs in the Kur, xii. 23; where it is commonly read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayota laka","text_ar":"هَيْتَ لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Zj;) but 'Alee and Ibn-'Abbás are said to have read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiy^otu laka","text_ar":"هِيْتُ لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with hemzeh. [See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hyA^","text_ar":"هيا"},{"kind":"text","text":".] (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayota","text_ar":"هَيْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is itself invariable whether used to denote the sing. or pl. or fem. or masc.; but the difference of number is observed in what follows it; for you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayota lakumaA","text_ar":"هَيْتَ لَكُمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Come ye two!"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayota lakun~a","text_ar":"هَيْتَ لَكُنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Come ye"},{"kind":"text","text":"women! &c.]: (S:) you also say simply"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayota","text_ar":"هَيْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Come!"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and this is also said to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hasten!"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Set forth journeying"},{"kind":"text","text":"through the land, or earth. (TA.) Authorities differ respecting this word; whether it be Arabic or arabicized; and whether it be a noun or a verb; &c. Accord. to AZ, as related by Az,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hyt lk","text_ar":"هيت لك"},{"kind":"text","text":"is arabicized in the Kur, from the Hebrew"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hytA kx","text_ar":"هيتا كخ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hytA kx","text_ar":"هيتا كخ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which I suppose to be meant for"},{"kind":"text","text":"עַהׇּה  לְבׇה"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ Now, come! ” occurring in Gen. xxxi. 44]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Akh","K","IB","TA","Zj","Fr","S","L","Ks"]},{"entry_id":"n41475","headword_ar":"هِيتٌ","root":"hyt","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depressed, piece of ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of ground having a low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depressed, bottom:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huw~apN","text_ar":"هُوَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwtapu","text_ar":"هُوتَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}